contentrichtext.text: '''IZ''', '''Iz''', or '''iz''' may refer to: *[[Arkia Israel Airlines]] (IATA code) *[[Iraq]] (NATO country code and FIPS 10-4 country code) *[[International zone]], a type of extraterritoriality governed by international law *[[Inclusionary zoning]], a zoning ordinance mandating affordable housing *[[Jacob Paek]], aka "IZ", a Korean American rapper *[[IZ (graffiti artist)]], aka "Iz the Wiz", an American graffiti artist *[[Israel Kamakawiwoʻole|Israel "Iz" Kamakawiwoʻole]], a Hawaiian musician and singer *[[iZ (toy)]], a musical toy released by Zizzle, L.L.C. in late 2005 *[[Iž]], an island in the Croatian part of the Adriatic Sea *[[The Trace (film)|Iz]], a 1994 Turkish film ==See also== *[[1Z (disambiguation)]] {{disambig}}
